<figureCitation id="137737C5FF90FF85FAABFB9866E5AB37" box="[1351,1421,1055,1079]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
