</figureCitation>
); anterior cercus wide or narrow, connected anteriorly and medially by large flat cercal expansion; posterior cercus elongated. Phallus (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF90FF85FE9FFBE062A9AB7F" box="[371,449,1127,1151]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
Figs. 
<number id="3D843967FF90FF85FE5DFBEF62A9AB7F" box="[433,449,1128,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="7.19">7</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF90FF85FE21FBE06283AB7F" box="[461,491,1127,1151]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1423,1446]" captionTargetBox="[272,1319,536,1402]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[267,1319,519,1402]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Macrostomus limbipennis (Bezzi), lectotype male. 12, left fore leg, posterior view; 13, left mid leg, anterior view; 14, left hind leg, anterior view; 15, right wing; 16 – 19, Peruvian male specimen; 16, wing; 17, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 18, terminalia, lateral view; 19, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Scales: 12 – 14 = 0.5 mm; 17 – 19 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281634/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">19</figureCitation>
, 
<number id="3D843967FF90FF85FE1AFBE06155AB7F" box="[502,573,1127,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="31.38">
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF90FF85FE1AFBE0617CAB7F" box="[502,532,1127,1151]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 31" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1369,1392]" captionTargetBox="[262,1324,665,1345]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[260,1328,663,1345]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 31. Macrostomus nigriventris (Macquart), holotype. 26, right mid leg, posterior view; 27, left wing; 28, apex of medial lobe of cercus; 29, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 30 terminalia, lateral view, setae omitted; 31, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view, setae broken, insertion indicated. Scales: 26 = 0.5 mm; 28 – 31 = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281636/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">31</figureCitation>
