).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF32B40FF90FF85FF2BFB286618AA57" blockId="1.[151,1437,581,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B938F752FF90FF85FF2BFB286276ABC7" bold="true" box="[199,286,1199,1223]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Female</emphasis>
. Head dichoptic; frons wider than anterior ocellus width; face narrower than frons, approximately half of anterior ocellus width. Legs with no pinnate scales; hind tarsomere 
<number id="3D843967FF90FF85FC40FB5460D2ABEB" box="[940,954,1235,1259]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
with one dorsal setae. Wing slightly wider than in male, usually more infuscated at costal and distal margin. Terminalia less shining and more gray pruinose than preabdomen. Tergite 
<number id="3D843967FF90FF85FE50FA9C62A2AA33" box="[444,458,1307,1331]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="8.0">8</number>
elongate. Sternite 
<number id="3D843967FF90FF85FD77FA9C61C1AA33" box="[667,681,1307,1331]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="8.0">8</number>
usually with median large sinus, laterally with ventral constriction. Genital fork with short to indistinct lateral arms. Spermatheca (
<figureCitation id="137737C5FF90FF85FCB7FAB860C4AA57" box="[859,940,1343,1367]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 25" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1184,1207]" captionTargetBox="[274,1332,485,1142]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[252,1334,483,1160]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 25. Macrostomus limbipennis (Bezzi), 20 – 25, Peruvian female specimen; 20, wing; 21, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 22, idem, lateral view; 23, idem, except cercus, ventral view; 24, genital fork and genital chamber; 25, oviduct and spermathecae. Scales: 21 – 23 = 0.2 mm; 24 – 25 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281635/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
Fig. 
<number id="3D843967FF90FF85FC63FAB860C4AA57" box="[911,940,1343,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
) with long duct and rounded receptacle.
</paragraph>
